<subSubSection id="464B00639D11DBB4DBD653216F006B70" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="C6705FB58F924EA89AE8583C89FF7F82" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
<taxonomicName id="9B668C7A93C2CCCE4A9FD04A79F4E145" LSID="178B5C6B-3D99-5FD1-BF87-2F21ACEE1858" authority="Agosti &amp; Collingwood, 1987" authorityName="Agosti &amp; Collingwood" authorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Messor" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Messor hellenius" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hellenius">Messor hellenius Agosti &amp; Collingwood, 1987</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="94AA3FF9E0AE051B0E8EEEB3C4640D49" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="288B39D86F0549026DFDA3F59AF7643E" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B15DBC921D317CCBAC083208FC06A1F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: Ograzhden Mt.: Drenovo vill., 06.04.2010, 7 w., leg. ALG; Churilovo vill., 10.09.2021, 1 q., 3 w., leg. ALG; East Rhodopes: Meden buk vill., 22.02.2012, 3 w., leg. ALG (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EF92944B188FDC74C387AF6E84A8BC49" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7727157" captionText="Figure 1. Messor hellenius, major lateral: dark specimen from Meden buk vill.; scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e83658.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/653851" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">1</figureCitation>
); Dolna Kula vill., 19.04.2012, 1 q., 3 w.; same place, 23.04.2021, 1 q., 15 w., leg. ALG; North Black Sea coast, Varna, Morska Gradina Park, 20.07.2017, 10 w., leg. ALG; Struma Valley, Lebnitsa vill., 06.08.2019, 13 w., leg. ALG (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C866EA254A445733603E0627A96E06C3" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7727161" captionText="Figure 2. Messor hellenius, major lateral: pale specimen from Lebnitsa vill.; scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e83658.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/653852" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">2</figureCitation>
); Burgas District, Tranak vill., 01.01.2021, 5 w., leg. M. Mohamed; Pirin Mt., Stara Kresna vill., 11.05.2021, 12 w., leg. ALG; Southern Black Sea coast: Chernomorets, 20.07.2006, 5 w., leg. and det. L. Borowiec (DBET); Primorsko, 27.05.2011, 6 w., leg. ALG; Maslen nos cape, 04.06.2021, 20 w., leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="73843A0CCFAC4389C74F9E94213910B2" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ADB5D86129A34517E37B4B45B123FF31" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="445EC99BBDE5FEC30A77E8FD1F58E385" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4AC2026AA51539E9A2067E72261D40BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
First record for Bulgaria. This species is known from Greece, the western coast of Anatolia and the European part of Turkey (
<bibRefCitation id="AF3CC2FBC72EC197449FC7B47B51ADC1" author="Salata, S." journalOrPublisher="Turkish Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="52 - 67" refId="B7725943" refString="Salata, S., Borowiec, L., 2019. Preliminary contributions toward a revision of Greek Messor Forel, 1890 (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Turkish Journal of Zoology 43: 52 - 67" title="Preliminary contributions toward a revision of Greek Messor Forel, 1890 (Hymenoptera: Formicidae)" volume="43" year="2019">Salata and Borowiec 2019a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B3FDA457F7704F1C66C101396439431E" author="Kiran, K." journalOrPublisher="Zoosystema" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="285 - 329" refId="B7725795" refString="Kiran, K., Karaman, C., 2020. Additions to the ant fauna of Turkey (Hymenoptera, Formicidae). Zoosystema 42 (18): 285 - 329" title="Additions to the ant fauna of Turkey (Hymenoptera, Formicidae)" volume="42" year="2020">Kiran and Karaman 2020</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="03F11B1118128B6CC75076E0D8574E4E" author="Borowiec, L." journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Silesiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 22" refId="B7725669" refString="Borowiec, L., Salata, S., 2018. New records of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Epirus, Greece. Acta Entomologica Silesiana 26: 1 - 22" title="New records of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Epirus, Greece" volume="26" year="2018">Borowiec and Salata (2018)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that the previous records of 
<taxonomicName id="B4B7A182EE2740C4D8B76E2A03435751" genus="M." lsidName="M. capitatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="capitatus">
<emphasis id="B9D5A6AE4D4057132696D38FE99C963F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">M. capitatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Latreille, 1798) from eastern parts of the Balkan Peninsula concern 
<taxonomicName id="FBFB6ABBA73D5943232C573761269832" genus="M." lsidName="M. hellenius" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="hellenius">
<emphasis id="F826F3FF602F2CBB0FE8020E2748DCC6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">M. hellenius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In this regard, it is very likely that the data on 
<taxonomicName id="858B80F4A6253925377BE09F38CD1777" genus="M." lsidName="M. capitatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="capitatus">
<emphasis id="88DD6748D465AA1CF51D00E321170F65" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">M. capitatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the northern Black Sea coast (
<bibRefCitation id="91057F063E4775AB7D578C382F05B2E9" author="Marko, B." journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="109 - 121" refId="B7725916" refString="Marko, B., Csosz, S., 2002. Die europaeischen Ameisenarten (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) des Hermannstaedter (Sibiu, Rumaenien) Naturkundemuseums I.: Unterfamilien Ponerinae, Myrmicinae und Dolichoderinae. Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 94: 109 - 121" title="Die europaeischen Ameisenarten (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) des Hermannstaedter (Sibiu, Rumaenien) Naturkundemuseums I.: Unterfamilien Ponerinae, Myrmicinae und Dolichoderinae" volume="94" year="2002">
<normalizedToken id="314DB49579630C0E7615080070FF2BD7" originalValue="Markó">Marko</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="030536A110EB80A55216BEFC851CBEB2" originalValue="Csősz">Csosz</normalizedToken>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
) refer to 
<taxonomicName id="404E8DC980A8338B7D62778C30E2B679" genus="M." lsidName="M. hellenius" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="hellenius">
<emphasis id="08DF799DC3B2E89BF91E93B9F4749EDE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">M. hellenius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
